@Teresa

My kids had a few different map puzzles that helped them learn geography. Now they do online games. My middle schooler can name and locate most countries now. He beats me when we get to Africa and Central Asia. We also played a lot of Ticket to Ride, which helped with the states. 

When it comes to the majority of my students, however, it can be frightening how little they know about where they are in relation to the rest of the world. Even basic geography, like which states border our state, can be a challenge for many of them.

@Teresa
